Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Pop a deep #saucepan{} (with a tight-fitting lid) on medium heat. Melt in the @butter{20%g}, then add the garlic and stir-fry for ~{1%minute}.

Stir in the @jasmine rice{150%g} until coated, ~{1%minute}. Add 1/4 tsp @salt{}, @water for the rice{300%ml} and bring to the boil. Once boiling, turn the heat down to medium and cover with the lid.

Leave the rice to cook for ~{10%minutes}, then remove the pan from the heat (still covered) and leave to the side for another ~{10%minutes} or until ready to serve (the rice will continue to cook in its own steam).

Meanwhile, trim and peel the @carrot{1}(trimmed and peeled). Use the #peeler{} to peel long ribbons down the length of the carrot, stopping at the core.

In a #medium bowl{}, combine the @rice vinegar{15%ml} and @sugar{1%tsp}. Season with @salt{}, then add the carrot. Mix together well, then set aside to pickle.

Pop a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat (no oil).

Once hot, lay the @duck breasts{2} in the pan, skin-side down, and fry until golden, ~{6-8%minutes}. Flip, then sear the other side for ~{1%minute} more.

Transfer to a #medium baking tray{}, skin-side up, season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}. Roast on the top shelf of your oven until cooked, ~{16-18%minutes}.

Once cooked, transfer to a #cutting board{} and rest for ~{5%minutes}. IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw duck and its packaging. It's fully cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, halve any thick broccoli stems lengthways.

Pop the @Tenderstem® broccoli{80%g} onto a #medium baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

Roast on the middle shelf until tender and crispy, ~{10-12%minutes}. If you'd prefer to boil your broccoli, boil it in step 5 while the sauce simmers for ~{3-4%minutes}, until tender.

> TIP: If you'd prefer to boil your broccoli, boil it in step 5 while the sauce simmers.

A few mins before everything's ready, heat the (now empty) frying pan on medium-high heat.

Add the @Szechuan paste{1%sachet}, @honey{15%g} and @water for the sauce{50%ml}. Bring to the boil, then simmer for ~{3-4%minutes}, until thickened and sticky.

> TIP: If your honey has hardened, pop in a bowl of hot water for 1 min.

Once the duck has rested, cut widthways into 1cm thick slices.

Fluff up the rice with a #fork{}, then share between your #bowls{} and arrange the sliced duck over one half.

Add the roasted broccoli and pickled carrot to the other half. Spoon the Szechuan sauce over the duck.

Drizzle the @mayonnaise{2%tbsp} over the top. Sprinkle with the @roasted white sesame seeds{5%g} and @crispy onions{1%sachet} to finish.

Enjoy!